# Safely Using Arrays
#
# Array - collection of elements identified by an index/key.
# contiguous memory locations -> good performance (cache friendly)
# same type data -> homogeneous data structure

# -fsanitize=address -> adress sanitizer -> detects memory errors
# -g produce additional debugging inflormation
# -01 allow minimal optimizations
# clang++ -std=c++14 -fsanitize=address -g -01 file.cpp
